{{One source|date=June 2018}} {{No footnotes|date=June 2018}} '''Subliterature''' or '''trivialliteratur''' is popular writing and texts that are sometimes called [[literature]] but not so classified by [[literary critics]]. Subliterature is intrinsically considered inferior to literature in terms of writing skill, depth and legacy. Subliterature is considered to have little influence on future literature despite any popular or commercial success. Characteristics of subliterature share some aspects of [[pop music]]: * Appeal to a general audience * Tendency to reflect existing trends rather than progressive developments.
==Examples of books considered subliterature== *''[[Harry Potter]]'' *''[[The Da Vinci Code]]'' *''[[Twilight (novel series)|Twilight]]'' *''[[Hush, Hush (series)|Hush, Hush]]'' *''[[Fifty Shades of Grey]]''
